-- Dortmund Beats Mainz to Go Top in Germany; Lazio Extends Its Lead in Italy
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2010-10-31T22:23:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-31/dortmund-wins-2-0-at-mainz-to-go-top-in-germany-lazio-leads-in-italy.html
Borussia Dortmund returned to the top
of German soccer’s Bundesliga with a 2-0 win at previous leader
Mainz yesterday.  Mario Goetze and Lucas Barrios got the goals as Dortmund
went a point ahead of Mainz in the standings. Eugen Polanski
missed a chance to make it 1-1 when his penalty kick was saved
by  Roman Weidenfeller .  Lazio leads by four points in Italy’s Serie A after a 1-0
win at Palermo yesterday. Brazilian defender Andre Dias scored
the 27th-minute winning goal to move Lazio to 22 points.  Inter Milan is second after a 1-0 win at Genoa three days
ago, while AC Milan is a point behind its city rival after a 2-1
home loss to Juventus two days ago.  In Spain, Villarreal failed to go level on points with
second-placed Barcelona after a 1-1 draw at Sporting Gijon
yesterday. Leader Real Madrid came back to win 3-1 at Hercules
two days ago and Barcelona is a point behind after a 5-0 home
win over Sevilla.  Montpellier failed to move into second place in the French
standings with a 1-1 draw against visitor Paris Saint-German
last night. Brest tops the table after a 2-0 home win over
Saint-Etienne two days ago.  In the Netherlands, Twente has a one-point lead after a 1-0
win at PSV Eindhoven yesterday. Twente has 28 points, with PSV
and Ajax -- a 4-1 winner at Heracles --  both on 27.  WEEKEND RESULTS
===============  Italy: Genoa 0-1 Inter Milan; AC Milan 1-2 Juventus; Roma 2-0
Lecce; Palermo 0-1 Lazio; Bari 0-2 Udinese; Brescia 0-1 Napoli;
Cagliari 2-0 Bologna; Cesena 0-1 Sampdoria; Parma 0-0 Chievo.
Late match: Catania 0-0 Fiorentina.  Spain: Valencia 1-1 Real Zaragoza; Hercules 1-3 Real Madrid;
Barcelona 5-0 Sevilla; Sporting Gijon 1-1 Villarreal; Deportivo
La Coruna 3-0 Espanyol; Racing Santander 4-1 Osasuna; Malaga 1-2
Real Sociedad; Atletico Madrid 1-1 Almeria. Late match: Athletic
Bilbao vs Getafe. Nov. 1: Real Mallorca 1-4 Levante.  Germany: Bayern Munich 4-2 Freiburg; Werder Bremen 2-3
Nuremberg; Wolfsburg 2-0 Stuttgart; Cologne 3-2 Hamburg;
Kaiserslautern 3-0 Borussia Moenchengladbach; St Pauli 1-3
Eintracht Frankfurt; Schalke 0-1 Bayer Leverkusen; Mainz 0-2
Borussia Dortmund; Hoffenheim 4-0 Hannover.  France: Auxerre 2-0 Nice; Caen 2-3 Nancy; Lorient 2-0 Arles-
Avignon; Lyon 2-1 Sochaux; Toulouse 1-1 Lens; Brest 2-0 Saint-
Etienne; Valenciennes 1-1 Lille; Monaco vs Bordeaux and
Marseille vs Rennes postponed (waterlogged). Late match:
